<h1>CMOS and RF Noise Metrics</h1>

<h2>Noise Figure (NF)</h2>
<p>Quantifies how much a device degrades the signal-to-noise ratio.</p>
<p>\[
NF = 10 \log_{10}\left(\frac{SNR_{in}}{SNR_{out}}\right)
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: dB</p>

<h2>Thermal Noise</h2>
<p>Generated by the random motion of electrons in a resistor.</p>
<p>\[
V_{n} = \sqrt{4kTBR}
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: V/√Hz</p>

<h2>Shot Noise</h2>
<p>Caused by the random arrival times of electrons at a barrier.</p>
<p>\[
I_{n} = \sqrt{2qI\Delta f}
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: A/√Hz</p>

<h2>Flicker Noise (1/f Noise)</h2>
<p>Has a frequency spectrum that is inversely proportional to frequency.</p>
<p>\[
I_{n} = K \cdot \frac{I_{D}}{f}
\]</p>
<p><strong>Units</strong>: A/√Hz</p>

